  "incidentDescription": "Multiple Arabic-language news outlets published reports describing the conflict in the Donbas region of southeastern Ukraine as 'military confrontations' that began in April 2015 between government forces and self-proclaimed Donetsk and Luhansk republics. The reports consistently frame the February 2014 Maidan events as a 'coup' and present the separatist republics' declaration of independence as occurring 'in the aftermath of the Ukrainian coup.' This framing delegitimizes Ukraine's post-2014 government by characterizing the democratic transition as an illegitimate seizure of power. The content was distributed across at least 21 different Arabic-language websites, including RT Arabic (Russian state media) and numerous regional Arabic news outlets, reaching Arabic-speaking audiences across multiple countries.",
